SECTION 4 — Food Chains
Definition, types and ecological significance
4.1 Definition
A food chain is a linear sequence of organisms through which nutrients and energy pass as one organism
eats another. Arrows in a food chain show the direction of energy flow (from eaten to eater). The
concept was described by Charles Elton (1927).
