SECTION 5 — Food Webs
Interconnected food chains — the real picture
5.1 Definition
A food web is a complex network of interconnected food chains within an ecosystem. In nature, most
organisms eat more than one type of food and are eaten by more than one type of predator. The food web
represents this real complexity. Term coined by Charles Elton (1927).
