n KEY FACTS FOR UGC NET — Unit 3.4
4 1. Energy flow is UNIDIRECTIONAL; Nutrient cycling is CYCLIC — most fundamental distinction
4 2. Lindeman's 10% Law (1942) — only 10% energy transferred between trophic levels
4 3. Pyramid of Energy is ALWAYS upright — no exception (Second Law of Thermodynamics)
4 4. Pyramid of Biomass is INVERTED in aquatic/ocean ecosystems (phytoplankton < zooplankton
biomass)
4 5. Ecological pyramids proposed by Charles Elton (1927) — called Eltonian pyramids
4 6. NPP = GPP - Plant Respiration. Tropical rainforest has highest NPP.
4 7. Grazing Food Chain starts with living plants; Detritus Food Chain starts with dead matter
4 8. In forest ecosystems, 80-90% energy flows through DFC (not GFC)
4 9. Carbon cycle = GASEOUS (atmospheric reservoir COn). Phosphorus = SEDIMENTARY (no
atmosphere)
4 10. Nitrogen fixation: Rhizobium (legumes, symbiotic), Azotobacter (free-living, aerobic)
4 11. Nitrification: Nitrosomonas (NHnn®NOnn) then Nitrobacter (NOnn®NOnn)
4 12. Denitrification: Pseudomonas/Thiobacillus (NOnn®Nn) — anaerobic process
4 13. Lichen = PIONEER species in Xerosere (rock succession)
4 14. First stage of Hydrosere = Phytoplankton stage (open water)
4 15. Climax community = final stable community; Sere = entire successional sequence
4 16. Clements (1916) proposed monoclimax theory; "sere" terminology
4 17. P is limiting nutrient in aquatic ecosystems; N is limiting on land
4 18. Acid rain: SOn + HnO ® HnSOn/HnSOn (from sulphur cycle disruption)
